Kazakhmys Says Profit Rose Last Year as Metal Prices Climbed

-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 
2011-03-29T06:55:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/kazakhmys-says-profit-rose-last-year-as-metal-prices-climbed-1-.html
Kazakhmys Plc (KAZ) ,  Kazakhstan ’s biggest
copper producer, said profit advanced last year as metals prices
climbed.  Underlying profit was $1.489 billion compared with $602
million a year earlier, as income attributable to equity holders
advanced to $1.45 billion from $554 million, London-based
Kazakhmys said in a statement today. Sales jumped 35 percent to
$3.2 billion. Copper advanced 30 percent last year.  The earnings include income from the company’s 26 percent
stake in Eurasian Natural Resources Corp.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Claudia Carpenter in London at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter in London at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  